  <heading>ST1B (vector plus immediate)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Scatter store bytes from a vector (immediate index)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction performs a scatter store
of  bytes from the Active elements of a vector register
to the memory addresses generated by a
 vector base plus immediate index.
The index is in the range 0 to 31.
Inactive elements are not written to memory.</para>
      <para>This instruction is illegal when executed in Streaming SVE mode, unless FEAT_SME_FA64 is implemented and enabled.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
    <sm_policy>SM_0_only</sm_policy>
    <is_store>True</is_store>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
